Actually, you're doing shuffling here, instead you should have UnstableOrderedIterable return OrderedPermutations.
the test I'd like to see here is one that basically reads:
Iterable<Integer> numbers = new UnstableOrderedIterable<>(ImmutableList.of(1, 2));
assertThat(ImmutableList.copyOf(numbers)).containsExactly(1, 2);
assertThat(ImmutableList.copyOf(numbers)).containsExactly(2, 1);

